[The etiology of this outbreak is undetermined. Chikungunya virus infection apparently has been ruled out by an unspecified test. It is not clear if laboratory tests have ruled out dengue virus infections. Involvement of the National Institute of Virology (NIV) is essential to determine which virus is involved in the outbreak if, indeed, a virus is responsible. ProMED would appreciate receiving the results of any tests done locally or at the NIV.

